The pr-review-toolkit's code-simplifier and comment-analyzer agents are
intentionally not migrated. code-simplifier was excluded because it
competes with the review-cycle loop's own fix application. comment-analyzer
was replaced by the cleanup subagent, which combines comment-policy review
with de-slopify cleanup application.

agents/code-reviewer.md and agents/silent-failure-hunter.md are unmodified
beyond their location in the filesystem.

agents/pr-test-analyzer.md and agents/type-design-analyzer.md were modified
by Oak OSS in version 0.7.0: pr-test-analyzer gained guidance that absent test
coverage for changed source is itself a finding, and type-design-analyzer
gained a type-boundary-smells section. See CHANGELOG.md for details.

When the plugin's review-cycle namespace applies, they are invoked as
`review-cycle:<agent-name>` instead of `pr-review-toolkit:<agent-name>`.
